Currently, two indicators are selected to measure the income of PV power generation, including the internal rate of return (IRR) and the whole life cost of power consumption. Here, IRR is the discount of net cash flow of PV power projects in 25 years (the average life cycle of PV power system), and the whole life cost of power consumption is the ratio of total cost of PV power projects to the total power generation in 25 years. Based on the analysis of influencing factors to these two PV revenue indicators, it shows that the cost of PV power generation can be calculated by the following Equation as Eq. (6).6Tcost=Cp1/Per+Rop+Rloan∗Rintr-Isub/Hfp\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
